goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between fertility rate and life expectancy.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of life expectancy across different countries.

goals.question: What is the predicted fertility rate for different countries?
goals.visualization: choropleth map of predicted fertility rate
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the predicted fertility rate for different countries and identify any patterns or trends.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility rate over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Fertility Rate'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility', y='life_expect', hue='country', legend='brief')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1), title='Country')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    median_life_expect = data['life_expect'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_life_expect, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_life_expect:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    data = data[['country', 'p_fertility']]
    data = data.groupby('country').mean().reset_index()
    world_data = world.merge(data, left_on='name', right_on='country')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 10))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    world_data.plot(column='p_fertility', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True, cax=cax)
    ax.set_title('What is the predicted fertility rate for different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='country', y='n_fertility', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('How does the normalized fertility rate compare across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Normalized Fertility Rate')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
